<div class="patternContent"><div class="patternTopic"> <h3><a name="Publications"></a> Publications </h3>
<p />
<p />
We are looking to cite those papers that have benefited from or contributed to the Open Science Grid. Please send such references to <a href="mailto&#58;osg&#45;contact&#64;opensciencegrid&#46;org">mailto&#58;osg&#45;contact&#64;opensciencegrid&#46;org</a>
<p />
<h3><a name="Citing_OSG_in_your_Publications"></a> Citing OSG in your Publications </h3>
<p />
<p />
Whenever you make use of Open Science Grid resources, services or tools, we would be grateful to have you acknowledge this use in any resulting publications. We suggest the following or similar text: 
<p />
<p />
"This research was done using resources provided by the Open Science Grid, which is supported by the National Science Foundation and the U.S. Department of Energy's Office of Science." 
<p />
<h3><a name="Scientific_Publications"></a> Scientific Publications </h3> <ul>
<li> Aguilar-Arevalo, A., A. Bazarko, S. Brice, B. Brown, L. Bugel, J. Cao, et al. 2007. A search for electron neutrino appearance at the &#916; m2 ~ 1 eV2 scale. <a href="http://www-boone.fnal.gov/publicpages/prl8.pdf" target="_top">http://www-boone.fnal.gov/publicpages/prl8.pdf</a> (April, 2007). 
</li> <li> Andreeva, J., S. Campana, F. Fanzago, J. Herrala, et al. 2008. High Energy Physics on the Grid: the ATLAS and CMS experience. Journal of Grid Computing 6:3-13.  
</li> <li> Benjamin, K., A. Schultz and D. Kofke. 2007. Virial coefficients of polarizable water: Applications to thermodynamic properties and molecular clustering. J. Phys. Chem. C 111:16021
</li> <li> Benjamin, K., A. Schultz and D. Kofke. "Fourth and Fifth Virial Coefficients of Polarizable Water", J. Phys. Chem. B, in press. 
</li> <li> Betten, Anton &amp; Betten, Deiter. 2008. There is No Drake/Larson Linear Space on 30 Points. Submitted for Publication.   * Blumenfeld, B., D. Dykstra, L. Lueking, E. Wicklund. 2007. CMS conditions data access using <span class="twikiNewLink">FroNTier<a href="/bin/edit/Main/FroNTier?topicparent=Main.ScientificPublications" rel="nofollow" title="FroNTier (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>. FERMILAB-CONF-07-526-CD. Proceedings of International Conference on Computing in High Energy and Nuclear Physics (CHEP 07) J. Phys.: Conf. Ser. in preparation.  
